The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, March 08, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, March 7: The government has decided to close down Tantusree and five other loss-making enterprises. 

 The public enterprises and industrial reconstruction department today wrote to UK?s Department for International Development seeking Rs 43 crore for early-retirement schemes. Besides Tantusree, West Bengal Ceramic Development Corporation, Pulver Ash Projects, Leather Industries Development Corporation, Electronic Tests and Development Centre and Mayurakshi Cotton Mills would be wound up. Tantusree, which has a retail chain selling saris, fabrics and furnishings, employs 605 people. The rest employ 700. 

 Midnapore: A school managing committee member was held and a teacher was said to be absconding after allegedly helping students cheat during the Madhyamik math paper. Sambhunath Pal and Dipak Mondal, were charged with beating up the headmaster of Ghatal?s Margopalpur High School because he protested.

 Calcutta: A man of about 60 and a woman were killed when a bus hit an autorickshaw on Diamond Harbour Road near Pailan. Eight others, including two children, were hospitalised.




